author: julianfoad
msg: On the 'move-tracking-2' branch: Add flexibility and verbosity in handling merge
conflicts in 'svnmover'. Make the merge have lenient "best guess" behaviour for
many potential conflict cases such as add-vs.-add (where the added content is
the same).
* subversion/svnmover/svnmover.c
(merge_conflict_policy_t): New.
(element_merge): Add flexibility and verbosity in handling merge conflicts.
(branch_merge_subtree_r): Use a minimally strict, compile-time constant policy.

author: stefan2
msg: * subversion/libsvn_fs_fs/revprops.c
(parse_packed_revprops): Remove revprop caching calls as it is
currently unavailable.

author: stefan2
msg: Eliminate another 50% of the revprop file header parsing overhead.
Unless we want to modify the pack file, i.e. write a revprop, we are not
interested in anything but a single revision's revprops.  So, add an
READ_ALL flag to the parser and let the callers decide what they need.
* subversion/libsvn_fs_fs/revprops.c
(parse_packed_revprops): Read the revprop location and size info only
if the READ_ALL flag is set.
(read_pack_revprop): Add READ_ALL parameter as a pass-through.
(svn_fs_fs__get_revision_proplist): We only need one set of revprops
and won't use the pack file contents
for anything else.
(write_packed_revprop): We need the full packed revprop info here.
